Sentencas: A feasible study for an in-situ stress evaluation method for solid oxide fuel cells based on Raman scattering spectroscopy was performed using two anode-supported cells with a cathode interlayer made from Samarium (Sm) doped ceria.
Titulo: Application of in-situ Raman scattering spectroscopy for stress condition measurement in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Model cells with a dense cathode interlayer demonstrated a compressive stress of -100s MPa at room temperature, and the results were comparable to those from X-ray diffraction.
Titulo: Application of in-situ Raman scattering spectroscopy for stress condition measurement in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Model cells with a porous interlayer showed complex stress conditions that deviated from in-plane stress due to their porosity, and the model cell was confirmed not to be suitable for this method.
Titulo: Application of in-situ Raman scattering spectroscopy for stress condition measurement in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At high temperatures, compressive stress was found to decrease as temperature increased and was almost neutral at the operating temperatures of the fuel cell, with good replication.
Titulo: Application of in-situ Raman scattering spectroscopy for stress condition measurement in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Hence, the feasibility of this method for model cells with a dense cathode interlayer was confirmed.
Titulo: Application of in-situ Raman scattering spectroscopy for stress condition measurement in solid oxide fuel cells
